var content_f40_14_41197=[" <div id=\"graphicsToolbar\">",
"  <div id=\"graphicsCopy\">",
"   &copy;2013 UpToDate",
"   <sup>",
"    &reg;",
"   </sup>",
"  </div>",
"  <div id=\"graphicsLinks\">",
"   <a href=\"?imageKey=NEPH%2F64698&amp;source=image_view&amp;view=print&amp;elapsedTimeMs=1\" onclick=\"\">",
"    <img alt=\"Print this page\" src=\"./../images/icn_print.myextg\" title=\"Print this page\"/>",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"icontxt textLink\" href=\"?imageKey=NEPH%2F64698&amp;source=image_view&amp;view=print&amp;elapsedTimeMs=1\" onclick=\"\" title=\"Print this page\">",
"    Print",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"etacLink\" href=\"#\">",
"    <img alt=\"Email graphic(s)\" src=\"./../images/icn_email.myextg\" title=\"Email graphic(s)\"/>",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"icontxt textLink etacLink\" href=\"#\" title=\"Email graphic(s)\">",
"    Email",
"   </a>",
"  </div>",
" </div>",
" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 470px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Filtration equilibrium and GFR",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 218px; background-image: url(data:image/gif;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Depiction of the hemodynamic forces along the length of the primate glomerular capillary. The dotted line represents the hydraulic pressure in Bowman's space, Pbs. The plasma oncotic pressure is added to this so that the middle solid line represents the sum of the forces retarding filtration: Pbs + -p. The upper solid line represents the glomerular hydraulic pressure (Pgc), and the shaded area depicts the net gradient favoring filtration, Pgc - Pbs - -p, which is +13 mmHg at the afferent arteriole. As a result of ultrafiltration of protein-free fluid, -p increases until the filtration gradient is abolished and filtration ceases. This is in contrast to muscle capillaries where filtration is limited by a decline in capillary hydraulic pressure.",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"    </div>",
"    <div class=\"reference\">",
"     Adapted from: Maddox, DA, Deen, WM, Brenner, BM, Kidney Int 1974; 5:271, and Deen, WM, Robertson, CR, Brenner, BM, Am J Physiol 1972; 223:1178. By permission from Kidney International.",
"    </div>",
"   </div>",
"  </div>",
" </div>",
"</div>"].join("\n");
